On Sat, 3 Aug 2002, Wim Van Sebroeck wrote:
>
> I just sent you 6 bitkeeper patches for the i8xx series chipsets.
Please don't use "bk send" to send me bitkeeper patches. They are totally
unreadable, they are harder to integrate than the alternatives (regular
patches or BK trees to be pulled), and they cause my inbox to have totally
nondescript Subject: lines, so I delete them automatically.
		Linus
